# COSS UI Rules

- Use COSS primitives and composition patterns from generated files before creating custom wrappers.
- Keep imports consistent with package exports (prefer `@afalambe/ui` for consumers).
- Preserve trigger/content hierarchies for overlay primitives (Dialog, Select, Popover, Tooltip, Menu).
- Keep accessibility props and semantic control types explicit (`button`, `input`, labels, aria attributes).
- Avoid API invention; follow generated component signatures and COSS docs.
- Import `@afalambe/ui/styles.css` once at app entry/layout before consuming UI components.
